    <string name="desc_wind">Wind speed measured at 10m height. High winds can affect drone stability and battery life. Threshold: > 25 km/h is dangerous.</string>
    <string name="desc_gusts">Sudden bursts of wind. Gusts are often more dangerous than constant wind for drone flight. Threshold: > 35 km/h is dangerous.</string>
    <string name="desc_wind_dir">Direction the wind is coming from. Important for takeoff and landing strategies.</string>
    <string name="desc_precip">Probability of rain or snow. Most consumer drones are not waterproof. Threshold: > 10% is risky.</string>
    <string name="desc_clouds">Percentage of the sky covered by clouds. Affects visibility and lighting for filming.</string>
    <string name="desc_visibility">Horizontal distance at which objects can be clearly seen. Critical for VLOS (Visual Line of Sight) flights.</string>
    <string name="desc_kp">Index representing geomagnetic activity. A high Kp index (> 4) can cause GPS interference and "flyaways".</string>
    <string name="desc_sunrise_sunset">Times when the sun rises and sets. Essential for legal night flight requirements and visibility.</string>
    <string name="desc_temp">Current ambient temperature. Extreme cold or heat affects battery performance and electronics.</string>
    <string name="desc_bz">Interplanetary magnetic field component. Negative Bz values can lead to magnetic storms affecting the drone\'s compass.</string>
    <string name="desc_sats">Number of satellites calculated by orbital prediction. Higher numbers ensure better stability.</string>
